line_1: Curious to know what was within contain'd,
line_2: With cautious Fear I search'd; my Fingers stain'd

line_1: And still within its flow'ry banks contain'd.
line_2: Full is his spreading current, but restrain'd.

line_1: All need requires is in that cot contain'd,
line_2: And much that taste untaught and unrestrain'd

line_1: Whose Quantity of Oil one Pot contain'd;
line_2: Yet num'rous Vessels fill'd, before 'twas drain'd.

line_1: So shall the ills the box contain'd —
line_2: Which Ether and the World profan'd —

line_1: In thee, vast ALL! are these contain'd,
line_2: For thee are those, thy parts ordain'd,
All that FANCY's self has seign'd,
